#. <html><head><meta charset="UTF-8"><meta content="Pali text from the Mahāsaṅgīti Tipiṭaka Buddhavasse 2500" name="description"><title></title></head><body><div id="text" lang="pli"><section class="sutta" id="pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs0.3"
msgid "Pācittiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on confession (<i lang=\"pli\">pācittiya</i>)"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs0.4"
msgid "Ovādavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 21"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs0.5"
msgid "21. Ovādasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on the instruction"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs0.6"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.50"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.21.1"></a> <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.263"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="484"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa "
"ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena therā bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo ovadantā lābhino honti "
"cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"At that time the senior monks who instructed the nuns were receiving robe-"
"cloth, almsfood, dwellings, and medicines."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.3"
msgid "Atha kho chabbaggiyānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—"
msgstr ""
"When the monks from the group of six found out about this, they thought,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.4"
msgid ""
"“etarahi kho, āvuso, therā bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo ovadantā lābhino honti "
"cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.5"
msgid "Handāvuso, mayampi bhikkhuniyo ovadāmā”ti."
msgstr "“Well then, let’s instruct the nuns.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.6"
msgid "Atha kho chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo upasaṅkamitvā etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "They then went to the nuns and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.7"
msgid "“amhepi, bhaginiyo, upasaṅkamatha; mayampi ovadissāmā”ti."
msgstr "“Come to us, Sisters, and we too will instruct you.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="485"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.8"
msgid "Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo yena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;"
msgstr ""
"Soon afterwards those nuns went to the monks from the group of six, bowed "
"down to them, and sat down to one side."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.9"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā chabbaggiye bhikkhū abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"But after giving just a short teaching, those monks spent the day on "
"pointless talk."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.10"
msgid ""
"Atha kho chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhunīnaṃ parittaññeva dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā "
"divasaṃ tiracchānakathāya vītināmetvā uyyojesuṃ—"
msgstr "They then dismissed the nuns, saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.11"
msgid "“gacchatha, bhaginiyo”ti."
msgstr "“Go, Sisters.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.12"
msgid ""
"Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhaṃsu."
msgstr ""
"Those nuns then went to the Master, bowed down to him, and stood to one side."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.13"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho tā bhikkhuniyo bhagavā etadavoca—"
msgstr "And the Master said to them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.14"
msgid "“kacci, bhikkhuniyo, ovādo iddho ahosī”ti?"
msgstr "“Nuns, I hope the instruction was effective?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.15"
msgid "“Kuto, bhante, ovādo iddho bhavissati."
msgstr "“Venerable Sir, how could the instruction be effective?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.16"
msgid ""
"Ayyā chabbaggiyā parittaññeva dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā divasaṃ tiracchānakathāya "
"vītināmetvā uyyojesun”ti."
msgstr ""
"After giving just a short teaching, the monks from the group of six spent "
"the day on pointless talk, and then dismissed us.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.17"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā tā bhikkhuniyo dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi samādapesi "
"samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi."
msgstr ""
"The Master instructed, inspired, and gladdened those nuns with a teaching."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.264"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.18"
msgid ""
"Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo bhagavatā dhammiyā kathāya sandassitā samādapitā "
"samuttejitā sampahaṃsitā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā "
"pakkamiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"The nuns  bowed down to the Master, circumambulated him with their right "
"side towards him, and departed."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="486"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.19"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṃghaṃ "
"sannipātāpetvā chabbaggiye bhikkhū paṭipucchi—"
msgstr ""
"The Master then had the Order of monks assembled and questioned the monks "
"from the group of six,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.20"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, bhikkhunīnaṃ parittaññeva dhammiṃ kathaṃ "
"katvā divasaṃ tiracchānakathāya vītināmetvā uyyojethā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you did this?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.21"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.22"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.23"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, bhikkhunīnaṃ parittaññeva dhammiṃ kathaṃ "
"katvā divasaṃ tiracchānakathāya vītināmetvā uyyojessatha."
msgstr ""
"“Foolish men, how can you give just a short teaching to the nuns, and then "
"spend the day on pointless talk, before dismissing them?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.24"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.25"
msgid "vigarahitvā … pe …"
msgstr "and after rebuking them …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.26"
msgid "dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:"

#. </p><div class="kamma"><p><a class="wt-pa" id="487"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.27"
msgid "“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bhikkhunovādakaṃ sammannituṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, you should appoint an instructor of the nuns."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.28"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, sammannitabbo."
msgstr "And this is how he should be appointed."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.29"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ bhikkhu yācitabbo."
msgstr "First a monk should be asked"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.30"
msgid "Yācitvā byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṃgho ñāpetabbo—"
msgstr "and then a competent and capable monk should inform the Order:"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.31"
msgid "‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr "‘Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.32"
msgid ""
"Yadi saṃghassa pattakallaṃ, saṃgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ bhikkhunovādakaṃ "
"sammanneyya."
msgstr ""
"If it seems appropriate to the Order, it should appoint monk so-and-so as an "
"instructor of the nuns."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.33"
msgid "Esā ñatti."
msgstr "This is the motion."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="488"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.34"
msgid "Suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr "Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.35"
msgid "Saṃgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ bhikkhunovādakaṃ sammannati."
msgstr "The Order appoints monk so-and-so as an instructor of the nuns."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.36"
msgid ""
"Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa bhikkhuno bhikkhunovādakassa sammuti, so "
"tuṇhassa;"
msgstr ""
"Any monk who approves of appointing monk so-and-so as an instructor of the "
"nuns should remain silent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.37"
msgid "yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya."
msgstr "Any monk who does not approve should say so."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="489"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.38"
msgid "Dutiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi … pe …"
msgstr "A second time I speak on this matter …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.39"
msgid "tatiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi—"
msgstr "A third time I speak on this matter:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.40"
msgid "suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr "Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.41"
msgid "Saṃgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ bhikkhunovādakaṃ sammannati."
msgstr "The Order appoints monk so-and-so as an instructor of the nuns."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.42"
msgid ""
"Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa bhikkhuno bhikkhunovādakassa sammuti, so "
"tuṇhassa;"
msgstr ""
"Any monk who approves of appointing monk so-and-so as an instructor of the "
"nuns should remain silent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.43"
msgid "yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya."
msgstr "Any monk who does not approve should say so."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="490"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.44"
msgid "Sammato saṃghena itthannāmo bhikkhu bhikkhunovādako."
msgstr "The Order has appointed monks so-and-so as an instructor of the nuns."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.45"
msgid "Khamati saṃghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti."
msgstr "The Order approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”"

#. </p></div><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.51"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="491"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.46"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā chabbaggiye bhikkhū anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā "
"dubbharatāya … pe …"
msgstr ""
"Then, after criticizing the monks from the group of six in many ways for "
"being difficult to support …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.47"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr ""
"the Master said, “And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.47a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="492"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.48"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu asammato bhikkhuniyo ovadeyya pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk who has not been agreed upon instructs the nuns, he commits an "
"offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.49"
msgid "(<em>21</em>:<strong>70</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection"><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.265"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="493"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs1.50"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.21.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="494"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs2.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena therā bhikkhū sammatā bhikkhuniyo ovadantā tatheva "
"lābhino honti cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"After being appointed to do so, the senior monks who instructed the nuns "
"still received robe-cloth, almsfood, dwellings, and medicines."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs2.2"
msgid "Atha kho chabbaggiyānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—"
msgstr "When they found out about this, the monks from the group of six said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs2.3"
msgid ""
"“etarahi kho, āvuso, therā bhikkhū sammatā bhikkhuniyo ovadantā tatheva "
"lābhino honti cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs2.4"
msgid ""
"Handāvuso, mayampi nissīmaṃ gantvā aññamaññaṃ bhikkhunovādakaṃ sammannitvā "
"bhikkhuniyo ovadāmā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Well then, let’s go outside the boundary, appoint each other as instructors "
"of the nuns, and then instruct them.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs2.5"
msgid ""
"Atha kho chabbaggiyā bhikkhū nissīmaṃ gantvā aññamaññaṃ bhikkhunovādakaṃ "
"sammannitvā bhikkhuniyo upasaṅkamitvā etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "After doing just that, they again went to the nuns and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs2.6"
msgid "“mayampi, bhaginiyo, sammatā."
msgstr "“Sisters, we too have been appointed."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs2.7"
msgid "Amhepi upasaṅkamatha."
msgstr "Come to us,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs2.8"
msgid "Mayampi ovadissāmā”ti."
msgstr "and we too will instruct you.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="495"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs2.9"
msgid "Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo yena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;"
msgstr "Once again the nuns went to the monks from the group of six"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs2.10"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā chabbaggiye bhikkhū abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu."
msgstr "and everything unfolded as before."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs2.11"
msgid ""
"Atha kho chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhunīnaṃ parittaññeva dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā "
"divasaṃ tiracchānakathāya vītināmetvā uyyojesuṃ—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs2.12"
msgid "“gacchatha, bhaginiyo”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs2.13"
msgid "Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs2.14"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhaṃsu."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs2.15"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho tā bhikkhuniyo bhagavā etadavoca—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs2.16"
msgid "“kacci, bhikkhuniyo, ovādo iddho ahosī”ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs2.17"
msgid "“Kuto, bhante, ovādo iddho bhavissati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs2.18"
msgid ""
"Ayyā chabbaggiyā parittaññeva dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā divasaṃ tiracchānakathāya "
"vītināmetvā uyyojesun”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs2.19"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā tā bhikkhuniyo dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs2.20"
msgid ""
"atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo bhagavatā dhammiyā kathāya sandassitā samādapitā "
"samuttejitā sampahaṃsitā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā "
"pakkamiṃsu."
msgstr ""

#. <a class="wt-pa" id="496"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs2.21"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṃghaṃ "
"sannipātāpetvā chabbaggiye bhikkhū paṭipucchi—"
msgstr ""
"The Master then had the Order of monks assembled and questioned the monks "
"from the group of six,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs2.22"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, bhikkhunīnaṃ parittaññeva dhammiṃ kathaṃ "
"katvā divasaṃ tiracchānakathāya vītināmetvā uyyojethā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you are acting like this?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs2.23"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs2.24"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs2.25"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, bhikkhunīnaṃ parittaññeva dhammiṃ kathaṃ "
"katvā divasaṃ tiracchānakathāya vītināmetvā uyyojessatha."
msgstr ""
"“Foolish men, how can you give just a short teaching to the nuns, and then "
"spend the day on pointless talk, before dismissing them?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs2.26"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …”…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs2.27"
msgid "vigarahitvā … pe …"
msgstr "and after rebuking them …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs2.28"
msgid "dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:"

#. </p><p class="rule">
#. This set of eight qualities is also found at AN8.52 <ref>MS.???.556</ref>, see NDB, pp.1192-93.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs2.29"
msgid ""
"“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, aṭṭhahaṅgehi samannāgataṃ bhikkhuṃ bhikkhunovādakaṃ "
"sammannituṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Monks, you should appoint a monk who possesses eight qualities as an "
"instructor of the nuns:"

#. </p><div class="sutta"><ul><li> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs2.30"
msgid ""
"Sīlavā hoti, pātimokkhasaṃvarasaṃvuto viharati ācāragocarasampanno "
"aṇumattesu vajjesu bhayadassāvī, samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu;"
msgstr ""
"He is virtuous and restrained by the monastic code. His conduct is good, he "
"associates with the right people, and he sees danger in minor faults. And he "
"undertakes and trains in the training rules."

#. </li><li><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.266"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs2.31"
msgid ""
"bahussuto hoti sutadharo sutasannicayo, ye te dhammā ādikalyāṇā "
"majjhekalyāṇā pariyosānakalyāṇā sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ "
"parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ abhivadanti tathārūpāssa dhammā bahussutā honti "
"dhātā vacasā paricitā manasā anupekkhitā diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā;"
msgstr ""
"He has learned much, and he retains and accumulates what he has learned. "
"Those teachings that are good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good "
"in the end, that have the right meaning and phrasing and which proclaim the "
"perfectly complete and pure spiritual life—he has learned many such "
"teachings, retained them in mind, recited them verbally, mentally "
"investigated them, and penetrated them well by view."

#. </li><li> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs2.32"
msgid ""
"ubhayāni kho panassa pātimokkhāni vitthārena svāgatāni honti suvibhattāni "
"suppavattīni suvinicchitāni suttaso anubyañjanaso;"
msgstr ""
"He has properly learned both monastic codes in detail, well analyzed them, "
"thoroughly mastered them, well investigated them in terms of the rules and "
"their detailed exposition."

#. </li><li> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs2.33"
msgid "kalyāṇavāco hoti kalyāṇavākkaraṇo;"
msgstr "He is well-spoken and has a good voice."

#. </li><li> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs2.34"
msgid "yebhuyyena bhikkhunīnaṃ piyo hoti manāpo;"
msgstr "He is generally liked by and pleasing to the nuns."

#. </li><li> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs2.35"
msgid "paṭibalo hoti bhikkhuniyo ovadituṃ;"
msgstr "He is capable of instructing the nuns."

#. </li><li>
#. VAR: panetaṃ → pana taṃ (?)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs2.36"
msgid ""
"na kho panetaṃ bhagavantaṃ uddissa pabbajitāya kāsāyavatthavasanāya "
"garudhammaṃ ajjhāpannapubbo hoti;"
msgstr "He has never committed a serious offense against a Buddhist nun."

#. </li><li> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs2.37"
msgid "vīsativasso vā hoti atirekavīsativasso vā—"
msgstr "He has been fully ordained for at least twenty years."

#. </li></ul></div><p><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.267"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs2.38"
msgid ""
"anujānāmi, bhikkhave, imehi aṭṭhahaṅgehi samannāgataṃ bhikkhuṃ "
"bhikkhunovādakaṃ sammannitun”ti."
msgstr ""
"Monks, you should appoint a monk who possesses these eight qualities as an "
"instructor of the nuns.”"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.52"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.21.3.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="497"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. </span>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr ""
"… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order "
"through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is "
"unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="498"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.1.6"
msgid "Asammato nāma"
msgstr "Who has not been agreed upon:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.1.7"
msgid "ñatticatutthena kammena asammato."
msgstr ""
"who has not been agreed upon through a procedure consisting of one motion "
"and three announcements."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="499"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.1.8"
msgid "Bhikkhuniyo nāma"
msgstr "Nuns:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.1.9"
msgid "ubhatosaṃghe upasampannā."
msgstr "they have been given the full ordination by both Orders."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="500"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.1.10"
msgid "Ovadeyyāti"
msgstr "Instructs:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.1.11"
msgid "aṭṭhahi garudhammehi ovadati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If he instructs in the eight rules to be respected, he commits an offense "
"entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.1.12"
msgid "Aññena dhammena ovadati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he instructs in any other teaching, he commits an offense of wrong "
"conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.1.13"
msgid "Ekatoupasampannaṃ ovadati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he instructs a nun who is fully ordained only on one side, he commits an "
"offense of wrong conduct."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="501"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.1.14"
msgid ""
"Tena sammatena bhikkhunā pariveṇaṃ sammajjitvā pānīyaṃ paribhojanīyaṃ "
"upaṭṭhāpetvā āsanaṃ paññapetvā dutiyaṃ gahetvā nisīditabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The monk who has been agreed upon should sweep the precincts, set out water "
"for drinking and for washing the feet, prepare a seat, get hold of a "
"companion, and then sit down."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.1.15"
msgid ""
"Bhikkhunīhi tattha gantvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīditabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The nuns should go there, bow down to the monk, and sit down to one side."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.1.16"
msgid "Tena bhikkhunā pucchitabbā—"
msgstr "The monk should then ask them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.1.17"
msgid "“samaggāttha, bhaginiyo”ti?"
msgstr "“Sisters, are you all present?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.1.18"
msgid ""
"Sace “samaggāmhāyyā”ti bhaṇanti, “vattanti, bhaginiyo, aṭṭha garudhammā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"If they say, “We’re all present, Venerable,” he should say, “Are you keeping "
"the eight rules to be respected?”"

#. </p><p>
#. VAR: niyyādetabbo → niyyātetabbo (itipi)
#. <i lang="pli">Niyyādetabbo</i>. For the meaning of this word in this context, see the usage in the origin story to the next rule, <ref>MS.2.517</ref>, and the explanation at <ref>Sp.4.792.10</ref>, <ref>Sp.4.800.25</ref>.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.1.19"
msgid "Sace “vattantāyyā”ti bhaṇanti, “eso, bhaginiyo, ovādo”ti niyyādetabbo."
msgstr ""
"If they say, “We are,” he should present the instruction, “This is the "
"instruction.”"

#. </p><p><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.268"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.1.20"
msgid "Sace “na vattantāyyā”ti bhaṇanti, osāretabbā."
msgstr "If they say, “We’re not,” he should recite the rules to be respected:"

#. <ul><li> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.1.21"
msgid ""
"“Vassasatūpasampannāya bhikkhuniyā tadahupasampannassa bhikkhuno abhivādanaṃ "
"paccuṭṭhānaṃ añjalikammaṃ sāmīcikammaṃ kātabbaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"“A nun who has been fully ordained for a hundred years should bow down to a "
"monk who was given the full ordination on that very day, and she should "
"stand up for him, put the palms of her hands together for him, and act "
"respectfully towards him."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.1.22"
msgid ""
"ayampi dhammo sakkatvā garukatvā mānetvā pūjetvā yāvajīvaṃ anatikkamanīyo."
msgstr ""
"This rule is to be honored and respected all one’s life, and is not to be "
"breached."

#. </li><li>
#. The Pali word behind the translation “monastery” is <i lang="pli">āvāsa</i>. This refers to the area within the <i lang="pli">simā</i>, the boundary, as established through a procedure. This area may be much larger than the space occupied by any actual buildings. 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.1.23"
msgid "Na bhikkhuniyā abhikkhuke āvāse vassaṃ vasitabbaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"A nun should not spend the rainy season in a monastery where there are no "
"monks."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.1.24"
msgid ""
"ayampi dhammo sakkatvā garukatvā mānetvā pūjetvā yāvajīvaṃ anatikkamanīyo."
msgstr ""
"This rule too is to be honored and respected all one’s life, and is not to "
"be breached."

#. </li><li>
#. VAR: paccāsīsitabbā → pac­cāsiṃ­si­tabbā (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.1.25"
msgid ""
"Anvaddhamāsaṃ bhikkhuniyā bhikkhusaṃghato dve dhammā paccāsīsitabbā "
"uposathapucchakañca ovādūpasaṅkamanañca, ayampi dhammo … pe …"
msgstr ""
"Every half-month a nun should ask the Order of monks for two things: about "
"the date of the observance day and about going for the instruction. This "
"rule too is to be honored and respected all one’s life, and is not to be "
"breached."

#. </li><li><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.269"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.1.26"
msgid ""
"vassaṃ vuṭṭhāya bhikkhuniyā ubhatosaṃghe tīhi ṭhānehi pavāretabbaṃ diṭṭhena "
"vā sutena vā parisaṅkāya vā;"
msgstr ""
"A nun who has completed the rainy-season residence should invite correction "
"from both Orders in regard to three things: what has been seen, what has "
"been heard, and what has been suspected."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.1.27"
msgid "ayampi dhammo … pe …"
msgstr ""
"This rule too is to be honored and respected all one’s life, and is not to "
"be breached."

#. </li><li>
#. Serious offense, <i lang="pli">garudhamma</i>, here refers to the <i lang="pli">saṅghādisesa</i> offenses, the offenses entailing suspension. 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.1.28"
msgid ""
"garudhammaṃ ajjhāpannāya bhikkhuniyā ubhatosaṃghe pakkhamānattaṃ caritabbaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"A nun who has committed a serious offense should undertake a trial period "
"towards both Orders for a half-month."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.1.29"
msgid "ayampi dhammo … pe …"
msgstr ""
"This rule too is to be honored and respected all one’s life, and is not to "
"be breached."

#. </li><li> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.1.30"
msgid ""
"dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhāya sikkhamānāya ubhatosaṃghe "
"upasampadā pariyesitabbā;"
msgstr ""
"A trainee nun who has trained in the six rules for two years may seek for "
"full ordination in both Orders."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.1.31"
msgid "ayampi dhammo … pe …"
msgstr ""
"This rule too is to be honored and respected all one’s life, and is not to "
"be breached."

#. </li><li> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.1.32"
msgid "na bhikkhuniyā kenaci pariyāyena bhikkhu akkositabbo paribhāsitabbo;"
msgstr "A nun may not in any way abuse or revile a monk."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.1.33"
msgid "ayampi dhammo … pe …"
msgstr ""
"This rule too is to be honored and respected all one’s life, and is not to "
"be breached."

#. </li><li>
#. “Correct” is here for <i lang="pli">vacanapatha</i>. For the meaning of this word see BVS, pp.73-76. 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.1.34"
msgid ""
"ajjatagge ovaṭo bhikkhunīnaṃ bhikkhūsu vacanapatho, anovaṭo bhikkhūnaṃ "
"bhikkhunīsu vacanapatho;"
msgstr ""
"From today onwards, nuns may not correct monks, but monks may correct nuns."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.1.35"
msgid ""
"ayampi dhammo sakkatvā garukatvā mānetvā pūjetvā yāvajīvaṃ anatikkamanīyo”ti."
msgstr ""
"This rule too is to be honored and respected all one’s life, and is not to "
"be breached.”"

#. </li></ul><p><a class="sc" id="19"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="502"></a>
#. This seems to say that if the nuns are all present then the monk must always give an <i lang="pli">ovāda</i> that consists in teaching the eight <i lang="pli">garudhammas</i>.This, however, needs to be seen in light of the further subdivision given in the text above, where the instruction in the <i lang="pli">garudhammas</i> is to be given only when the nuns say they are not practicing them.If the nuns are practicing the <i lang="pli">garudhammas</i>, there seems to be no restriction on the nature of the <i lang="pli">ovāda</i>. 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.1.36"
msgid ""
"Sace “samaggāmhāyyā”ti bhaṇantaṃ aññaṃ dhammaṃ bhaṇati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If they say, “We’re all present, Venerable,” and he instructs them with "
"another teaching, then he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.1.37"
msgid ""
"Sace “vaggāmhāyyā”ti bhaṇantaṃ aṭṭha garudhamme bhaṇati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If they say, “We’re not all present, Venerable,” and he instructs them in "
"the eight rules to be respected, then he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. According to the commentary (<ref>Sp.4.800.25</ref>) this simply means not having said, “Sisters, this is the instruction,” <i lang="pli">ovādaṃ aniyyādetvāti eso bhaginiyo ovādoti avatvā</i>. This, however, does seem contrived. A more natural meaning might be to see this statement in conjunction with the previous one, and the two together might then be paraphrased as follows: If the nuns say they are not all present, then one should not instruct in the eight rules to be respected, nor in any other teaching. In any case, once “Sisters, this is the instruction” has been said, it seems any teaching can be given; see origin story to the next rule, <ref>MS.2.517</ref>.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.1.38"
msgid "Ovādaṃ aniyyādetvā aññaṃ dhammaṃ bhaṇati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he does not present the instruction, but he gives them another teaching, "
"then he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="20"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.53"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.21.3.2"></a> <a class="wt-pa" id="503"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.270"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.2.1"
msgid ""
"Adhammakamme adhammakammasaññī vaggaṃ bhikkhunisaṃghaṃ vaggasaññī ovadati, "
"āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is an illegitimate procedure and he perceives it as illegitimate, and  "
"the Order of nuns is incomplete and he perceives it as incomplete, then if "
"he instructs those nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.2.2"
msgid ""
"Adhammakamme adhammakammasaññī vaggaṃ bhikkhunisaṃghaṃ vematiko ovadati, "
"āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is an illegitimate procedure and he perceives it as illegitimate, and "
"the Order of nuns is incomplete but he is unsure if it is, then if he "
"instructs those nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.2.3"
msgid ""
"Adhammakamme adhammakammasaññī vaggaṃ bhikkhunisaṃghaṃ samaggasaññī ovadati, "
"āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is an illegitimate procedure and he perceives it as illegitimate, and "
"the Order of nuns is incomplete but he perceives it as complete, then if he "
"instructs those nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="21"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="504"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.2.4"
msgid ""
"Adhammakamme vematiko vaggaṃ bhikkhunisaṃghaṃ vaggasaññī ovadati, āpatti "
"pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is an illegitimate procedure but he is unsure if it is, and the Order "
"of nuns is incomplete and he perceives it as incomplete, then if he "
"instructs those nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.2.5"
msgid ""
"Adhammakamme vematiko vaggaṃ bhikkhunisaṃghaṃ vematiko ovadati, āpatti "
"pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is an illegitimate procedure but he is unsure if it is, and the Order "
"of nuns is incomplete but he is unsure if it is, then if he instructs those "
"nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.2.6"
msgid ""
"Adhammakamme vematiko vaggaṃ bhikkhunisaṃghaṃ samaggasaññī ovadati, āpatti "
"pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is an illegitimate procedure but he is unsure if it is, and the Order "
"of nuns is incomplete but he perceives it as complete, then if he instructs "
"those nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="22"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="505"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.2.7"
msgid ""
"Adhammakamme dhammakammasaññī vaggaṃ bhikkhunisaṃghaṃ vaggasaññī ovadati, "
"āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is an illegitimate procedure but he perceives it as legitimate, and "
"the Order of nuns is incomplete and he perceives it as incomplete, then if "
"he instructs those nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.2.8"
msgid ""
"Adhammakamme dhammakammasaññī vaggaṃ bhikkhunisaṃghaṃ vematiko ovadati, "
"āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is an illegitimate procedure but he perceives it as legitimate, and "
"the Order of nuns is incomplete but he is unsure if it is, then if he "
"instructs those nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.2.9"
msgid ""
"Adhammakamme dhammakammasaññī vaggaṃ bhikkhunisaṃghaṃ samaggasaññī ovadati, "
"āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is an illegitimate procedure but he perceives it as legitimate, and "
"the Order of nuns is incomplete but he perceives it as complete, then if he "
"instructs those nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="23"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="506"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.2.10"
msgid ""
"Adhammakamme adhammakammasaññī samaggaṃ bhikkhunisaṃghaṃ vaggasaññī ovadati, "
"āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is an illegitimate procedure and he perceives it as illegitimate, and "
"the Order of nuns is complete but he perceives it as incomplete, then if he "
"instructs those nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.2.11"
msgid ""
"Adhammakamme adhammakammasaññī samaggaṃ bhikkhunisaṃghaṃ vematiko ovadati, "
"āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is an illegitimate procedure and he perceives it as illegitimate, and "
"the Order of nuns is complete but he is unsure if it is, then if he "
"instructs those nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc21:pts-cs3.2.12"
msgid ""
"Adhammakamme adhammakammasaññī samaggaṃ bhikkhunisaṃghaṃ samaggasaññī "
"ovadati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
